  "title": "Dental Surgery Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Work Location: Hougang, Singapore </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Working Hours: 5-day work week (Max. 44 hours per week) | 3 different shifts (9am to 1pm, 2pm to 5pm, 6pm to 9pm) </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Monthly Salary: Up to S$2,700 (Negotiable) </strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support the Dentist in all aspects of patient care, including getting the appropriate instruments and materials required, and ensuring patient comfort throughout the treatment.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the cleaning and sterilisation of instruments and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Carry out stock checks to ensure all necessary supplies are available.</li>\n  <li>Perform front desk duties with courtesy and professionalism, including booking and managing appointments, attending to walk-on and phone enquiries, registering patients, billing and collecting payments.</li>\n  <li>Maintain clinic cleanliness to ensure a welcoming environment for our patients.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prior experience in dental assisting is a plus, but not required. We provide comprehensive on-the-job training for those new to the field.</li>\n  <li>Positive Attitude: A cheerful disposition and a can-do attitude.</li>\n  <li>Team Player: Strong team collaboration skills.</li>\n  <li>Multitasking: Able to multitask in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Technical skills: Computer literacy</li>\n  <li>Flexibility: Willing to work night shifts and weekends</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Nextbeat Singapore Pte.Ltd.</p>\n<p>EA License Number: 22C1267</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22107133</p>\n<p><br></p>",
